FBIS4-10398 "drlat070_b_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-070 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 Haiti Senators, Party Leaders Criticize Resolution Senators, Party Leaders Criticize Resolution RDC Leader: Implementation `Illegal' FL1104213394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1700 GMT 11 Apr 94 FL1104213394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Text] The implementation of Article 149 is illegal. That was a statement by Eddy Volel of the Christian Democratic Assembly [RDC]. Volel says President Aristide has been acknowledged as president, so the country cannot be led by two presidents. [Begin Volel recording, in Creole] ...of Emile Jonassaint, whom they want to put in power through Article 149, is illegal, unconstitutional, and contrary to the people's will. Raoul Cedras and the Army acknowledged Aristide as president twice, on 16 December 1990 and on 3 July 1993. [end recording] That was RDC leader Eddy Volel.
